Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stagflation refers to a simultaneous increase in inflation an decrease in gross domestic product (GDP). Haln 7.25 It's also characterized by slow economic growth, high unemployment, and rising prices. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Understanding Stagflation Stagflation was long believed to be impossible because widely accepted economic theories from the 19th century ruled out such a model. The Great Depression and emergence of Keynesian economics caused economists to reevaluate inflation and unemployment. Stagflation is an example of how economic data can sometimes conflict with popular theories and policies. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Causes of Stagflation Oil Prices A sudden increase in oil prices reduces a country's economic output. The Gold Standard President Nixon removed the gold standard, removing commodity backing for the U.S. dollar. Poor Economic Policies Strict regulation of markets, goods and labor. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Why is Stagflation Bad? Slow economic growth should lead to an increase in unemployment, but not an increase in prices. Stagflation contradicts this notion. With rising unemployment and inflation there is a decrease in consumer spending power. There is less money to spend and all money being worth less and less. Investopedia'.
